It's a five-for as well! SN Thakur b Andrew Tye 0(1)

Commentary Text: Andrew Tye to Ankit Sharma, out Caught by Brendon McCullum!! That's been skied up .. and McCullum takes a really good catch around 5 yards inside the ropes. It was there to be slogged from a length, but Ankit went through it too early and lobbed a leading edge up which surprisingly travelled quite a fair bit. Commentary Text: Basil Thampi to Smith, no run, Smith is down. Right in the ribcage and the RPS skipper is withering in pain. Short delivery and it was the back of the hand slower one, Smith was early into the pull, missed it by a long way and is struck right under his chest. Grunted in pain as soon as he was hit and went to ground immediately. Thampi checks on him even as the physio comes out. Smith is back on his feet. He is going to continue and that's a good sign for Pune

Commentary Text: Andrew Tye to Tripathi, out Caught by Finch!! A breezy innings comes to an end. One shot too many from Tripathi. Should have tried to bat a bit longer, especially with Smith at the other end. Full delivery on off, Tripathi makes a bit of room and lofts it to mid-off. The idea was to go over the fielder, but with the ball being too close to his bat, he did not get the elevation. Finch reverse cups it right on the edge of the circle. Commentary Text: P Kumar to Rahane, out Caught by Raina!! What a way to start your 150th IPL game. First, won the toss and now pulls off a blinder. Even he can't believe that he has plucked that out. A blob for Rahane and early trouble for Pune. This one jagged back in from a shortish length, Rahane thought it would be shaping away and went for a flashy cut, the outside edge flies towards the cordon. Raina, standing at wide slip, reacts quickly and grabs it with his left hand. He caught it when the ball had almost passed him. Rahane c Raina b P Kumar 0(3)

Commentary Text: Stokes to Brendon McCullum, 2 runs, goodness me! Rahul Chahar has pulled off one of the finest moments of this IPL. Remember Smith's superman dive when he was playing for Pune Warriors? Chahar is barely 18 and look what he has done? Brendon McCullum DILSCOOPED this after shuffling across his off-stump...Chahar at third man, moves quickly to his left, jumps as high as he can while facing towards the boundary ropes, flicks the ball back into play mid-air and saves 4 runs for his side. Stunning!
